 still present around the world, the story of how Kazakhs gave up their nuclear inheritance holds urgent lessons for global security.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNuclear disarmamentzKazakhstanxHistory. 0aNuclear weaponsxGovernment policyzKazakhstanxHistory. 0aNuclear weaponszKazakhstanxHistory. 0aNuclear weaponszKazakhstanxTestingxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Arms Control.2bisacsh  aCentral Asia.  aDenuclearization.  aDisarmament.  aKazakhstan.  aNuclear Testing.  aNuclear Weapons.  aNuclear diplomacy.  aSoviet Union.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362993640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503629936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503629936/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099451-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-PLWb2022